We believe in the ability of Talent to have a platform where they can transact safely, efficiently, and with low transaction fees. For Nebulai Talent is an asset, it is the engine for innovation, and the fuel for society to move forward.
We are building the first Catalyst Platform in the world. Our Decentralized Solutions and Talent Marketplace (DSTM) also referenced as Nebulai Marketplace is a dynamic ecosystem where Companies, Talent, Solution Providers, and Investors can gather to commerce seamlessly by leveraging Web 3 technologies.
We are creating a Decentralized Autonomous Organization (DAO) that will handle the governance of the Nebulai Marketplace. The main objective for our TDAO is to introduce a feedback loop for our decision making as an organization and for the advancement of the Nebulai Marketplace. The second objective is to have a thriving community of Talent that can benefit from the social, collaborative, and network effect of participating on the TDAO. This DAO intends to allow the Nebulai community of Talent which includes developers, IT professionals, business users, and other non-technical people to gather in an active community and have the ability to vote on proposals submitted by the DAO to shape the future of the Nebulai Marketplace and its community of Talent. 
The Nebulai Talent DAO (TDAO) will have several objectives including:
Nebulai Marketplace Governance: 

All members of the TDAO can acquire Nebulai Governance Tokens (NGT) for purposes of having rights to vote on the future of the Nebulai Marketplace. These voting rights allows the TDAO to submit and vote on proposals that affect the following areas of the Nebulai Marketplace:
1)	Governance Voting where the TDAO is a Consulted Decision Maker:

o	Roadmap & Features: Nebulai will ask the TDAO to vote on matters related to the future roadmap of the Nebulai Marketplace. These may include new and features and functionality to be deprecated. The TDAO is also able to submit proposals to be considered and voted on by Nebulai and the TDAO.

o	Rules & Guidelines: Nebulai will ask the TDAO to vote on matters of modifying or adding rules and guidelines for the operation on the Nebulai Marketplace. The TDAO is also able to submit proposals to be considered and voted on by Nebulai and the TDAO.

o	Decision Tie Breaker: From time to time, and whenever there is a proposal decision where Nebulai Corp deems appropriate to request feedback from the TDAO, Nebulai will submit a Decision Tie Breaker proposal and the TDAO will be the tie breaker of this decision.

2)	Governance Voting where the TDAO is the Main Decision Maker:
Nebulai Talent Community: The main purview of the TDAO is to propose and vote on matters related to the Nebulai Talent Community. These include but are not limited to propose on:
o	Community Leads and Members: The TDAO is open for anyone that wishes to join the community. The TDAO will start with an initial set of Community Leads and Members which will be selected by Nebulai based on their contributions and collaboration with the project. TDAO will decide who should be promoted, demoted, or removed. 

o	Events and Gatherings: The TDAO may propose when, where, and how often the community should meet and define if the meetings are to be held in person, hybrid, or online meetings. TDAO will host varied events including hackathons, promotional and recreational events, and celebratory events. By default, all gatherings should be held in hybrid mode, meaning there should always be an online version for the whole community to attend regardless of geographic location.

o	Priority Topics and Projects: The TDAO may propose the top priority topics for the community which may vary from time to time as technology evolves and the community may want to focus on different initiatives. This includes where the TDAO sees Nebulai helping by bringing together thought leaders and other support to help the TDAO's onboarding and readiness. 

o	Moderation: The TDAO should moderate its own members, content, and conduct. The TDAO will organically be moderated by the TDAO community leads who will decide and have admin permissions to the different communication channels available for the community. As a general guideline, the Nebulai Community should be an open, unbiased, fair, and equitable place where people can openly discuss ideas related to the community, its projects, and other topics of relevance. It should be inadequate for the community to discuss topics around politics, religion, or other polarizing topics unless they have direct impact into the community priority matters which shall be decided and moderated by the Nebulai community leads.
The Nebulai DAO Introduction and Structure

Let us start by introducing what a DAO is and then proceed to explain how Nebulai plans to use this mechanism to be able to create a dynamic Talent community focused on the next generation of technologies.
Decentralized Autonomous Organizations (DAOs): According to Jack du Rose, co-founder of Colony (1), a DAO “is a type of decentralized application which incentivizes its users to engage in activity which furthers its agreed business objectives by enabling them to work together without requiring them to trust one another”. (Colony (2019) <https://colony.io>)
For Nebulai a DAO is a type of organization that is assembled for common purposes in which the decision making of the organization is fully or partially orchestrated by computer programs called “smart contracts.” Decisions, record keeping, and financial transactions can then be kept in the blockchain for purposes of transparency. The DAO can combine the use of programmatic decision making through Smart Contracts or human decision making that later is stored as part of the record keeping of the DAO. A combination of both is also possible, where the DAO makes some programmatic decisions and others are done by humans.
The Nebulai Talent DAO is a hybrid DAO where proposals, record keeping, and financial transactions are both managed by Smart Contracts and Humans. The main objective for our TDAO is to introduce a feedback loop for our decision making as an organization and for the advancement of the Nebulai Marketplace. The second objective is to have a thriving community of Talent that can benefit from the social, collaborative, and network effect of participating on the TDAO.
In summary, the TDAO is a platform and a collective intelligence organization where its members get together to interact, collaborate, and make decisions based on a self-enforcing open protocol, leveraging the functionality of Smart Contracts as a mechanism to perform voting for proposals, and the Blockchain as a ledger for record keeping of resolutions, financial transactions, and other documentation relevant to the operation of the DAO.
